  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b86\u0b95\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bcd \u0b87\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc1 : \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc6\u0bb9\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0baf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Solution to shortage of medicines by the end of August: Health Minister Kehalia",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Health Minister Keheliya Rambukwella has said that the current shortage of medicines in the country will be completed in August.",
        "Minister Keheliya Rambukwella also said that now the economic and political crises have been resolved to some extent and the country is returning to normalcy.",
        "Minister Keheliya said the above during a meeting with the Japanese Ambassador to Sri Lanka, Minukoshi Hideki, and UNICEF representatives.",
        "The first phase of pharmaceuticals worth 1.5 million dollars to be provided by the Japanese government to Sri Lanka was officially handed over to the Minister of Health by the Japanese Ambassador on Thursday.",
        "These include medicines for high blood pressure, diabetes, heart disease, kidney disease, liver disease, etc.",
        "Diabetes and calcium are also found, especially for pregnant women. The value of the first batch of drugs handed out yesterday is $107,650.",
        "These are provided by the Government of Japan through UNICEF. The event was also attended by UNICEF Deputy Representative to Sri Lanka Emma Brinkam and representatives from Japan.",
        "All allies around the world are supporting Sri Lanka's recovery from the crisis. The Health Minister also expressed his gratitude to those countries.",
        "He said that all the countries in the region have extended support in a very friendly manner and among them Japan has provided high level of friendship.",
        "He pointed out that the support given especially during the Covid crisis and in the current crisis is very important and the ongoing discussions with the International Monetary Fund are successful.",
        "The Minister mentioned that the arrival of tourists has increased marginally in the last week and that all the problems can be resolved in the near future. The minister also pointed out that unique success can be achieved by facing these challenges.",
        "During the drug crisis, the priorities to be given were classified and dealt with appropriately as per the advice of the experts of the health sector.",
        "The Minister of Health pointed out to the foreign delegation that it is important to give priority to children and expectant mothers, self-manage emergency treatments and equipment, reschedule non-urgent surgeries and better management. He also mentioned that Triposha scheme can be restarted in the country."
      ],
